NAME=help
FILE=-
CMDS=<<EOF
!!../bin/r2flutter -h
?e ===
!!r2 -NN -q -i ../src/r2/core_flutter.dylib -qc 'r2flutter -h' -
EOF
EXPECT=<<EOF
Usage: ../bin/r2flutter [options] <libapp_path_or_dir>
Modifiers:
  -h                    Show help
  -j                    Output in JSON format
  -r                    Format output for r2 commands
  -V                    Show version
  -q                    Suppress non-essential output
  -v                    Verbose (stderr debug info)
  -vv                   More verbose (dump headers)
Actions:
  -c                    Print extracted class information
  -f                    Print all extracted functions (addr name)
  -H                    Print Dart AOT snapshot header info
  -i                    Print instruction table entries to stdout
  -R                    Print radare2 script for snapshot analysis
  -s                    Print all extracted strings
  -T                    Print string-based type names
  -x                    Print metadata/data-image xrefs
Options:
  -l <N>                Limit output to N items
  -n                    Heuristic fallback for unknown functions; may assign wrong names
  -o <file>             Load Flutter obfuscation map JSON
===
Usage: r2flutter [-ajirfqncFstxH] [args]
| r2flutter          analyze dart snapshot and apply flags/comments
| r2flutter -a       run Dart-aware code analysis and recover code refs
| r2flutter -c       dump classes as JSON
| r2flutter -C       apply Dart classes, fields, methods and types
| r2flutter -F       include field info in class output
| r2flutter -f [n]   list first N discovered functions (default 20)
| r2flutter -H       dump Dart AOT snapshot header info
| r2flutter -i       dump instruction table entries to output
| r2flutter -j       dump snapshot header as JSON
| r2flutter -n       use heuristic name-pool fallback; names may be wrong
| r2flutter -q       analyze quietly (no extra output)
| r2flutter -r       output r2 script (like rabin2 -r)
| r2flutter -s       dump all strings as JSON
| r2flutter -t       dump strings as r2 comments
| r2flutter -x       dump metadata/data-image xrefs
EOF
RUN
